WEBVTT

00:11.011 --> 00:14.431
KIRINOSHIMA JUNIOR HIGH SCHOOL

00:16.891 --> 00:18.226
Yo! Yo, Koyuki.

00:22.272 --> 00:23.106
Hey.

00:23.189 --> 00:24.816
Which one of us do you think is the
hottest?

00:24.899 --> 00:25.734
It's me, right?

00:26.401 --> 00:28.111
Huh? Well, um...

00:30.321 --> 00:31.698
Man, you're so cute.

00:32.699 --> 00:34.826
You got her all flustered, Tatsu.

00:34.909 --> 00:35.827
Look at that!

00:36.703 --> 00:38.788
They only mess with you because
you let them.

00:38.872 --> 00:40.373
Stop letting them rile you up!

00:40.874 --> 00:42.167
Oh... O-Okay.

00:44.294 --> 00:45.253
That looks so good.

00:46.337 --> 00:47.756
Ah, my bad, Koyuki.

00:47.839 --> 00:48.965
Didn't notice you there.

00:49.049 --> 00:50.675
Maybe you shouldn't be so short.

00:52.719 --> 00:53.553
Help out, Amano.

00:53.636 --> 00:55.805
Let shorty here borrow some of your
height!

00:57.432 --> 00:58.767
Could he be any more obvious?

00:58.850 --> 01:00.435
Yeah, everyone can tell.

01:00.518 --> 01:01.352
Right?

01:03.313 --> 01:04.272
Shorty, shorty!

01:04.355 --> 01:05.690
Wait up, Shorty Yuki!

01:07.442 --> 01:08.860
Chill, I was just joking!

01:09.861 --> 01:11.404
I've always asked myself...

01:11.905 --> 01:14.991
Ooh, Igarashi definitely has a crush
on you, Koyuki.

01:15.492 --> 01:17.786
I think Tatsu has a thing for you too.

01:17.869 --> 01:19.913
Ugh, lucky! I'm so jealous!

01:20.580 --> 01:24.250
Why's it alright just 'cause someone
likes you, or claims they're joking?

01:35.553 --> 01:37.931
Why don't... my feelings matter?

01:46.397 --> 01:48.024
MEITEN HIGH SCHOOL

01:48.108 --> 01:50.401
Mari, Muko, and Mei!

01:52.070 --> 01:53.238
Okay! Then everyone's in!

01:53.321 --> 01:54.155
It's happening!

01:54.239 --> 01:57.117
Last day of finals, we're having
ourselves a snack party!

01:57.700 --> 01:58.535
- Yay!
- Yay!

01:58.618 --> 01:59.452
Yay!

02:00.203 --> 02:01.830
- Love it!
- What should we bring?

02:01.913 --> 02:04.874
- Girl, this was such a great idea!
- Class Five is so lucky.

02:04.958 --> 02:07.544
- I'm excited.
- Azumi's a goddess who walks among us!

02:07.627 --> 02:11.339
And she even talks to us lowly introverts
because she's basically a saint!

02:12.632 --> 02:13.466
Excuse me.

02:14.259 --> 02:15.260
- Huh?
- Huh?

02:18.138 --> 02:18.972
Here.

02:20.473 --> 02:21.683
The teacher asked...

02:22.225 --> 02:24.435
If I could make sure to bring this
to you.

02:27.355 --> 02:28.481
Uh, well...

02:29.482 --> 02:30.316
Thank you?

02:34.362 --> 02:36.322
- She's terrifying.
- She's terrifying.

02:36.406 --> 02:37.574
Who was that?

02:37.657 --> 02:40.160
Koyuki Hikawa... aka the Ice Queen.

02:40.660 --> 02:41.661
The Ice Queen?!

02:42.162 --> 02:44.414
She doesn't hang out with any other
students.

02:44.497 --> 02:46.749
That's the first time I've ever talked to
her.

02:46.833 --> 02:49.711
- But it's almost the third trimester.
- It's not my fault.

02:49.794 --> 02:52.297
She gives off these prickly "back off"
vibes, so I just kept my distance.

02:52.380 --> 02:53.339
Chick's scary, man.

02:57.927 --> 03:00.930
Whenever Miki invites people to stuff,
everyone wants to come!

03:01.014 --> 03:03.516
- Oh my gosh, stop!
- 'Cause she's the idol of class five!

03:03.600 --> 03:04.434
Stop!

03:04.517 --> 03:07.478
Look, come on, you guys, stop acting
like I'm some kind of...

03:33.755 --> 03:34.964
It's already winter.

03:36.382 --> 03:38.760
Which means the second trimester's
almost over.

03:39.594 --> 03:42.430
One more to go before my first year
of high school ends.

03:43.973 --> 03:44.933
Without...

03:45.975 --> 03:47.477
Anything really happening.

03:51.105 --> 03:54.192
Well... I guess it's better than middle
school at least.

03:55.151 --> 03:55.985
Oh...

03:56.861 --> 03:57.695
Hmmm.

03:59.447 --> 04:03.534
For the most part I don't care how people
see me anymore, but it kinda bothers me

04:03.618 --> 04:05.828
when they look at me like that.

04:06.871 --> 04:09.374
I don't get it.
What on earth's so scary about me?

04:10.375 --> 04:11.209
My face?

04:13.836 --> 04:15.171
Should I smile more?

04:15.255 --> 04:16.464
SQUISH

04:23.137 --> 04:23.972
Whoa!

04:26.849 --> 04:27.684
Oh...

04:28.226 --> 04:29.102
Sorry, sorry!

04:29.894 --> 04:32.146
I was just curious what you were doin'
there.

04:32.981 --> 04:34.565
Minato, what's going on?

04:34.649 --> 04:36.192
Oh. Yota! What's up?

04:36.276 --> 04:38.069
Huh? Hey, what're you doing?

04:38.152 --> 04:39.195
Are you bullying her?

04:39.279 --> 04:41.030
That's so not cool, man, c'mon!

04:41.114 --> 04:42.073
Who, me? Please.

04:42.573 --> 04:43.658
Are you okay?

04:43.741 --> 04:44.867
Let me help you up.

04:46.119 --> 04:47.412
Oh, uh... thanks.

04:48.162 --> 04:48.997
I mean...

04:53.584 --> 04:54.460
So tall!

04:55.044 --> 04:56.587
152 cm, 176 cm, 189 cm

04:56.671 --> 04:59.716
Sorry about my friend here. You can't
take him anywhere.

04:59.799 --> 05:02.593
What're you apologizing for? I didn't
do anything.

05:02.677 --> 05:04.053
Is he telling the truth?

05:04.137 --> 05:06.347
Seriously, what kinda guy do you
think I am?

05:07.307 --> 05:08.933
Y'always seemed cool to me, Hikawa.

05:09.017 --> 05:10.184
We never had problems.

05:10.727 --> 05:13.187
Aside from making weird faces, you're
pretty chill.

05:13.271 --> 05:15.857
- What?
- Sorry again about scaring you there.

05:17.734 --> 05:19.152
Well. See ya.

05:27.327 --> 05:29.078
How did he know my name?

05:29.871 --> 05:30.747
More importantly...

05:31.706 --> 05:32.540
Who was that?

07:08.928 --> 07:11.848
I saw this on the stream yesterday.
Did you know it's going like super viral

07:11.931 --> 07:12.807
right now?

07:12.890 --> 07:14.517
Whoa. Really? I didn't know that.

07:14.600 --> 07:16.144
- Someone's sitting in my seat.
- Where do they sell it?

07:16.227 --> 07:17.478
At convenience stores, mostly.

07:17.562 --> 07:18.980
Which is less effort?

07:19.063 --> 07:20.648
THE EFFORT TO SPEAK UP

07:21.816 --> 07:23.025
Yeah... I'll just wait.

07:31.075 --> 07:32.869
Oh my gosh! Am I sitting in your seat?!

07:32.952 --> 07:33.786
I'm so sorry!

07:33.870 --> 07:35.538
GRADE 1 CLASS 2

07:35.621 --> 07:36.873
Uh... no, it's fine.

07:39.125 --> 07:40.126
Awkward...

07:44.005 --> 07:46.132
I- I'm really sorry about that, Hikawa.

07:46.215 --> 07:47.383
Huh?

07:48.718 --> 07:49.677
What for?

07:53.181 --> 07:55.683
I'm confused.
Did something merit an apology?

08:05.359 --> 08:06.777
Koyun, did you leave yet?

08:08.863 --> 08:10.615
Not yet. I'm still at the entrance.

08:11.616 --> 08:13.868
I don't have work today. Let's walk home
together!

08:13.951 --> 08:14.785
Woohoo!

08:15.745 --> 08:17.413
Okey-doke. I'll be at my locker.

08:17.914 --> 08:19.040
Be right there.

08:20.082 --> 08:22.168
Ten... nine... eight...

08:22.668 --> 08:23.503
What? A countdown?!

08:23.586 --> 08:24.504
Seven.

08:24.587 --> 08:25.505
Wait, hold on!

08:32.303 --> 08:35.139
Six, five, four, three...

08:36.432 --> 08:37.266
Two...

08:37.767 --> 08:39.560
- One.
- Koyun!

08:49.529 --> 08:50.363
Safe!

08:55.660 --> 08:56.869
Hey! What's so funny?

08:56.953 --> 08:57.828
What is it?

08:57.912 --> 09:00.414
I just didn't think you'd take
it seriously.

09:00.498 --> 09:02.750
That is probably my quickest time
on record!

09:02.833 --> 09:04.085
Pretty impressive, huh?

09:06.295 --> 09:08.464
You can be such a goofball, Miki.

09:10.675 --> 09:12.134
Can I hang out at your place?

09:12.885 --> 09:14.762
Sure, my mom's not home anyway.

09:15.304 --> 09:18.516
Oh, and by the way, you know you
ignored me in the hallway yesterday,

09:18.599 --> 09:19.433
right?

09:19.517 --> 09:20.351
BLANK STARE

09:20.434 --> 09:23.271
Because I didn't have anything to
say to you at the time.

09:23.354 --> 09:25.189
- Uh...
- You could've at least said hi!

09:25.731 --> 09:26.941
Isn't Miki amazing?

09:27.441 --> 09:28.484
What social skills!

09:28.568 --> 09:30.611
She can even connect with the Ice Queen.

09:35.491 --> 09:37.535
Look, they're all good people, and...

09:38.035 --> 09:39.870
I like them, I do, but...

09:40.580 --> 09:41.872
I just don't get it!

09:41.956 --> 09:44.041
They put me up on this weird pedestal.

09:44.792 --> 09:47.670
It's like everyone thinks I walk on
water or something!

09:48.337 --> 09:50.047
Why? I don't get it!

09:50.548 --> 09:53.759
I'd rather go back to being treated
like a gorilla, like before.

09:53.843 --> 09:56.137
Insult me, or call me names! Anything!

09:56.846 --> 09:58.806
I wanna be silly and goof around.

09:58.889 --> 10:02.018
I just really don't wanna play
Little Miss Perfect anymore!

10:02.101 --> 10:03.686
I wanna make people laugh.

10:04.270 --> 10:05.271
As the real me!

10:06.981 --> 10:10.568
Then why don't you just start acting like
yourself around our classmates?

10:10.651 --> 10:12.236
Instead of this persona.

10:12.737 --> 10:15.698
I'm not trying to put on the whole sweet
act on purpose.

10:16.240 --> 10:17.491
Ahh, I don't know.

10:17.575 --> 10:21.120
Whenever I try to be my real self,
for some reason, it just doesn't

10:21.203 --> 10:22.038
come out.

10:22.705 --> 10:25.374
At school, I automatically switch to
that mode.

10:29.754 --> 10:30.588
Maybe...

10:31.922 --> 10:34.216
Maybe I don't even know who the real me
is.

10:34.717 --> 10:37.053
Or what my real feelings even are.

10:41.724 --> 10:42.558
Mi-

10:42.642 --> 10:44.518
BANG

10:44.602 --> 10:46.437
- ...ki?
- Ugh, oh my gosh!

10:46.937 --> 10:48.689
Just snap out of it, Miki!

10:48.773 --> 10:50.733
I'm being such a sappy, emo drama queen.

10:50.816 --> 10:52.818
I promise I won't let it happen again!

10:54.362 --> 10:55.821
You'll be just fine.

10:56.739 --> 11:00.326
Whether you're an idol or a gorilla,
your true friends will always stay

11:00.409 --> 11:01.243
by your side.

11:02.119 --> 11:05.456
Those who weren't there for the right
reasons might lose interest,

11:05.539 --> 11:06.957
but who cares about them?

11:07.041 --> 11:07.958
Koyun...

11:08.459 --> 11:09.418
If it were me...

11:10.628 --> 11:14.924
I'd honestly rather be all by myself...
than keep fake friends around.

11:15.633 --> 11:16.467
What?

11:16.550 --> 11:19.261
If I didn't talk to anyone all day I'd
literally die!

11:19.762 --> 11:21.555
Dunno about literally, but sure.

11:22.306 --> 11:25.935
I really wish I had the strength to enjoy
being alone as much as you do.

11:26.894 --> 11:28.562
Well, I dunno about all that.

11:28.646 --> 11:30.523
I'm not saying my way's right either.

11:31.399 --> 11:34.652
Always taking others' feelings into
account is really admirable.

11:37.279 --> 11:39.448
But if it's too much for you, you
can stop.

11:45.454 --> 11:47.081
THE WAY YOU SEE YOURSELF

11:50.501 --> 11:53.379
Ugh, I can't think about this kinda
stuff right now!

11:53.462 --> 11:55.881
Alright. Let's go back to studying for
the test.

11:57.174 --> 11:58.134
Sounds like a plan.

11:58.217 --> 12:00.845
Sweet, now go ahead and tell me
everything that'll be on the

12:00.928 --> 12:02.596
- English exam.
- English!

12:02.680 --> 12:03.514
Seriously?

12:12.022 --> 12:15.025
I love the quiet of the classroom before
everyone gets here.

12:15.818 --> 12:17.611
Now where's my vocabulary book...

12:18.612 --> 12:19.447
Hm?

12:20.990 --> 12:22.616
This is Miki's.

12:24.910 --> 12:27.621
She must've left it after our
study session yesterday.

12:28.622 --> 12:31.584
I imagine she'll need it, so I should
bring it back to her.

12:32.793 --> 12:36.172
Miki probably isn't here yet,
so guess I'll just put it in her desk

12:36.255 --> 12:37.089
drawer for now.

12:40.468 --> 12:41.302
Huh?

12:49.477 --> 12:50.311
Whoa!

12:58.944 --> 12:59.820
Gotcha.

13:01.030 --> 13:03.199
That was terrifying.

13:04.033 --> 13:04.867
Are you okay?

13:06.410 --> 13:07.995
Oh, the guy from the other day.

13:08.078 --> 13:08.913
- Huh?
- Uh-huh?

13:08.996 --> 13:09.830
Wait...

13:11.040 --> 13:12.625
Huh? W-What is it?

13:12.708 --> 13:13.918
Ooh, no, no, no.

13:14.585 --> 13:15.586
What is...

13:16.712 --> 13:18.214
What's going on here?

13:20.800 --> 13:21.675
Go on, Koyuki.

13:22.176 --> 13:23.761
Feed Mr. Giraffe.

13:31.936 --> 13:32.770
Ohhh!

13:34.688 --> 13:36.106
The girl from the other day!

13:36.732 --> 13:38.150
Um. I am.

13:38.234 --> 13:41.612
I'm not wearing my contacts today,
so I didn't recognize you.

13:41.695 --> 13:43.531
Sorry for bumping into you.

13:43.614 --> 13:44.657
Are you okay?

13:48.077 --> 13:50.287
Uh, I just had a flashback.

13:51.497 --> 13:52.331
Oh, wait.

13:54.333 --> 13:55.167
Hmm.

13:55.751 --> 13:57.253
Are you friends with Miki?

13:57.795 --> 13:58.921
Uh. Yeah.

14:00.339 --> 14:01.173
He knows Miki?

14:02.174 --> 14:03.551
Are you in class 5, Sir?

14:04.051 --> 14:07.263
No, I'm in class six actually.
Was just coming to get a textbook I

14:07.346 --> 14:08.180
WHY ARE YOU USING HONORIFICS?

14:08.264 --> 14:10.391
lent to my friend in class five.

14:11.058 --> 14:12.935
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

14:13.435 --> 14:16.105
I came to give this back to her since she
forgot it.

14:17.857 --> 14:18.691
Oh.

14:19.441 --> 14:20.901
W- Where is her desk?

14:21.777 --> 14:22.736
Seriously?

14:24.655 --> 14:25.489
I think, uh...

14:25.573 --> 14:27.908
- This is probably it.
- Probably?

14:27.992 --> 14:28.868
I'm messing with you.

14:28.951 --> 14:29.785
This is it.

14:29.869 --> 14:32.204
Hey, you wanna scribble something on
her desk?

14:32.955 --> 14:34.707
Like "don't forget this next time."

14:35.249 --> 14:36.083
No.

14:36.166 --> 14:37.334
I'll just text her.

14:37.835 --> 14:39.962
Yeah, but who wants to be all mature?

14:40.045 --> 14:42.673
I prefer writing little notes for
my friends.

14:42.756 --> 14:44.967
Like "I got my textbook back."

14:47.720 --> 14:50.180
He seems... pretty laid back.

14:51.181 --> 14:52.016
See you later.

14:52.600 --> 14:54.101
I really appreciate your help.

14:54.810 --> 14:56.812
Let's both crush our final exams.

14:56.896 --> 14:58.147
Uh, what was it?

14:58.230 --> 14:59.523
Let's see, um...

15:00.649 --> 15:02.568
- Himuro!
- Oh. Um.

15:03.068 --> 15:05.279
My name isn't Himuro, though...

15:05.362 --> 15:06.530
It's Hikawa.

15:07.197 --> 15:08.574
Oh, well. It's okay.

15:09.116 --> 15:10.910
He just met me so that makes sense.

15:23.672 --> 15:25.841
So peaceful... and quiet.

15:26.675 --> 15:27.635
Just how I like it.

15:31.680 --> 15:34.183
- A huge coffee stain right in the
- Guys always hang out in groups.

15:34.266 --> 15:35.100
Middle of his shirt. So I try to tell

15:35.184 --> 15:37.311
- him, right? But he's all like
- Depends on the guy, I guess.

15:37.394 --> 15:38.729
"Concentrate, Mr. Hayato!"

15:38.812 --> 15:40.064
- And I'm like, dude...
- Hm?

15:40.147 --> 15:40.981
I recognize him.

15:41.065 --> 15:43.400
He was with the guy who looked like a
giraffe.

15:45.194 --> 15:46.111
He's in my grade.

15:46.195 --> 15:48.197
There's three grades at my school.

15:49.490 --> 15:52.368
I never paid much attention to my
surroundings before.

15:52.910 --> 15:55.371
Didn't know who my classmates were.

15:55.454 --> 15:57.957
- Eventually, I was just like fine
- Or anything about them, really.

15:58.040 --> 16:00.668
Whatever, and let him keep
walking around like that.

16:02.962 --> 16:03.796
Oops.

16:04.421 --> 16:07.132
Our eyes met. I think. Maybe.

16:10.594 --> 16:13.889
I just quickly looked away like an
awkward weirdo.

16:14.515 --> 16:17.309
Then again, I barely know him, so why
would I say hi?

16:20.354 --> 16:21.355
Eh, it's fine.

16:22.356 --> 16:24.733
Let's see. We've got milk tea...

16:25.609 --> 16:27.194
Oh, cocoa sounds good too.

16:27.277 --> 16:28.862
MADE WITH 8 AUTHENTIC SPICES

16:29.613 --> 16:30.447
What's up?

16:32.825 --> 16:34.410
Why'd you ignore me back there?

16:35.577 --> 16:38.872
- Oh, I did?
- Yeah, I waved at you, and you ran away.

16:39.832 --> 16:41.542
Huh? You waved?

16:42.042 --> 16:43.085
I can't believe it!

16:43.168 --> 16:45.045
Ah! Uh, I'm- I'm sorry.

16:45.629 --> 16:46.463
Am I though?

16:46.964 --> 16:49.675
Uh, I honestly just didn't notice you
had waved.

16:49.758 --> 16:51.510
I swear I didn't mean anything by it.

16:51.593 --> 16:53.721
I know. Just messin' with ya.

16:53.804 --> 16:55.556
- Huh?
- Your drink.

16:56.306 --> 16:57.141
Oh, yeah.

16:58.142 --> 17:00.728
BIMMY AUTHENTIC CURRY DRINK
EIGHT KINDS OF SPICES

17:00.811 --> 17:02.438
What's that? You like that stuff?

17:02.521 --> 17:04.648
No, I just pressed the button by mistake.

17:05.357 --> 17:06.900
Oh, man, that was my fault.

17:06.984 --> 17:09.361
- I'm so sorry.
- This guy...

17:10.195 --> 17:12.281
He doesn't seem like a bad person.

17:13.615 --> 17:16.994
But his way of keeping people at
arms length is different from mine.

17:17.077 --> 17:17.911
Hiya!

17:18.871 --> 17:22.666
So I can't help but keep my guard up
and feel wary.

17:23.625 --> 17:25.753
I can't tell... who you really are.

17:27.254 --> 17:28.088
Hey!

17:29.214 --> 17:30.924
Whatcha gettin' into, Amamiya?

17:31.717 --> 17:32.593
Amamiya?

17:32.676 --> 17:33.677
Hm?

17:33.761 --> 17:35.637
Right, I never introduced myself.

17:35.721 --> 17:38.682
Name's Amamiya.
Nice to officially meet you.

17:39.183 --> 17:42.269
- Uh, hi.
- Wait, why're you introducing yourself?

17:42.352 --> 17:43.395
You hitting on her?

17:43.479 --> 17:45.105
Wait, whoa, what's going on?

17:46.482 --> 17:49.693
I know he seems all cute and cuddly but
be warned, alright?

17:49.777 --> 17:52.029
You better keep an eye out with this one.

17:52.112 --> 17:53.238
Nah, I'm just playin'!

17:54.281 --> 17:56.241
Okay, knock it off. For real.

17:56.325 --> 17:57.409
- Uh...
- Get lost, dude.

17:57.493 --> 17:59.078
- No, thanks.
- I'm uncomfortable.

17:59.161 --> 18:00.162
Jeez...

18:00.704 --> 18:03.207
And I really, really don't like it.

18:04.291 --> 18:06.752
Huh? Uh, what's going on? You good?

18:06.835 --> 18:07.669
Hm.

18:09.213 --> 18:10.756
STRETCH

18:11.256 --> 18:12.299
What?

18:12.382 --> 18:13.300
What is happening?

18:14.301 --> 18:16.220
Oh. Wait, I think...

18:16.720 --> 18:18.180
He's teasing me.

18:18.931 --> 18:19.973
MIND THEATER
THE CORRECT WAY TO RESPOND WHEN TEASED

18:20.057 --> 18:22.142
Okay, so what's the right way to respond?

18:23.060 --> 18:24.186
One: Get angry.

18:24.269 --> 18:25.687
Rah, I'm so angry!

18:26.188 --> 18:27.439
Two: Act shy.

18:27.523 --> 18:29.358
Oh, my gosh, would you stop?

18:30.526 --> 18:31.652
Three: Laugh.

18:31.735 --> 18:32.986
You're so funny.

18:34.530 --> 18:35.489
It's probably best...

18:40.035 --> 18:41.245
To just smile.

18:41.745 --> 18:43.080
Option three: Laugh.

18:43.163 --> 18:43.997
Hahaha.

18:52.089 --> 18:53.382
Man, is she prickly.

18:53.966 --> 18:57.594
Or was she just like that 'cause
she was mad at me because I interrupted

18:57.678 --> 18:58.595
your conversation?!

18:58.679 --> 19:00.013
No, probably not.

19:03.308 --> 19:04.560
If I were to guess...

19:05.686 --> 19:08.021
That was... her wall?

19:18.240 --> 19:19.324
Hey, help her out, Amano!

19:19.408 --> 19:21.618
Let shorty here borrow some of your
height!

19:21.702 --> 19:22.870
Yeah, yeah...

19:24.746 --> 19:26.498
Yo, 'sup, Little Yuki!

19:32.671 --> 19:34.089
Tell me the truth, Koyuki.

19:34.173 --> 19:35.507
Are you into Igarashi?

19:42.222 --> 19:43.724
I mean, did you see that?

19:44.391 --> 19:45.517
That was so funny!

19:46.351 --> 19:47.186
I died!

19:51.732 --> 19:53.317
I'm sorry, Koyuki.

20:04.703 --> 20:06.955
I'm warning you, don't try it.

21:57.190 --> 21:58.025
Hm?

21:58.817 --> 22:00.485
Koyun, I'm sorry!

22:00.569 --> 22:02.904
Homeroom is literally never gonna end!

22:03.905 --> 22:06.616
You can just head to the community center
without me.

22:06.700 --> 22:07.868
Great.

22:09.244 --> 22:10.662
- Hey. Hey, hey! Why are you all
- Ugh.

22:10.746 --> 22:11.830
By yourself, huh?

22:11.913 --> 22:12.831
I'm not.

22:12.914 --> 22:13.999
Could've fooled me!

22:14.082 --> 22:15.375
I don't see anyone else.

22:15.459 --> 22:18.295
- Yeah, where are they then?
- Why is it always like this?

22:18.378 --> 22:20.213
- Is it an imaginary friend?
- Why me?

22:20.756 --> 22:22.966
Why do I still get bullied and
harassed even after school?

22:23.050 --> 22:24.593
She can exorcise my demons!

22:24.676 --> 22:25.761
Yo, wait up!

22:27.471 --> 22:29.097
Hey, we're just tryna help you out here!

22:29.181 --> 22:30.349
We're really nice guys.

22:31.266 --> 22:33.226
I dunno, speak for yourself, man.

22:34.644 --> 22:37.356
- I mean, I'm just sayin...!
- I really hate this feeling.

22:40.025 --> 22:41.401
It's the absolute worst.

22:42.486 --> 22:44.404
- No, but seriously you can trust us.
- This is bad.

22:44.488 --> 22:46.323
Yeah, like I said, we're nice guys. Don't
worry.

22:46.406 --> 22:47.240
I have to run.

22:54.623 --> 22:55.499
FREEZE

22:56.124 --> 22:57.376
I don't know his name.

22:57.459 --> 22:59.086
GONG

22:59.169 --> 23:01.463
- Uh, is she broken?
- Uh.

23:01.546 --> 23:02.381
Um...

23:02.464 --> 23:03.298
THINKING

23:03.382 --> 23:04.800
- Help!
- What's your problem?

23:05.467 --> 23:06.301
You know him?

23:07.427 --> 23:09.471
- Hm?
- Oh! He saw!

23:09.554 --> 23:10.389
STARE

23:10.472 --> 23:11.306
Hm? Hmmm?

23:11.973 --> 23:13.141
Put your contacts in!

23:16.728 --> 23:17.854
And... he's gone.

23:18.355 --> 23:21.566
- Dude, he totally blew you off!
- Ouch, he ignored you so hard. Jeez!

23:21.650 --> 23:24.319
- Now come on, let's go have some fun.
- I'm not going!

23:25.237 --> 23:26.655
Oh, what should I do?

23:26.738 --> 23:29.157
TWO PEOPLE AGAINST ONE
WHAT IF I MAKE THEM MAD IN A BAD WAY?

23:29.241 --> 23:30.117
And frustrated.

23:30.617 --> 23:32.285
- Come on.
- And pissed off!

23:32.369 --> 23:34.371
- Let's go. Let's go. Let's go!
- It'll be super fun!

23:34.454 --> 23:36.206
I told you... I'm not going anywhere!

23:36.289 --> 23:38.417
- Yeah, trust us!
- Just leave me alone.

23:38.917 --> 23:40.127
Seriously.

23:43.130 --> 23:43.964
Bye.

23:46.925 --> 23:48.135
Sorry. Are you okay?

23:48.969 --> 23:51.638
Oh! I knew it. It was you!

23:52.889 --> 23:54.099
Mister Giraffe.
